name: Common Core Ontologies Building Blocks
abstract:
Building blocks for the Common Core Ontologies (CCO) suite - a mid-level ontology extending 
Basic Formal Ontology (BFO) with eleven domain-agnostic ontologies for representing entities 
across all domains of interest.
description:
This repository contains building blocks for the **Common Core Ontologies (CCO)** version 2.0,
a widely-used suite of eleven ontologies that extend the Basic Formal Ontology (BFO), an ISO 
standard top-level ontology.

The eleven CCO ontologies include:

- **Agent Ontology**: Representation of agents (persons, organizations) and their roles
- **Artifact Ontology**: Representation of manufactured objects, models, and functions
- **Currency Unit Ontology**: Representation of currencies and monetary amounts
- **Event Ontology**: Representation of processes and activities performed by agents
- **Extended Relation Ontology**: Relations between entities at the CCO level
- **Facility Ontology**: Representation of buildings and infrastructure
- **Geospatial Ontology**: Representation of locations and spatial regions
- **Information Entity Ontology**: Representation of information content and metadata
- **Quality Ontology**: Representation of attributes, qualities, and measurements
- **Time Ontology**: Representation of temporal regions and relations
- **Units of Measure Ontology**: Representation of standard measurement units

CCO has been designated as a baseline standard for formal ontology development by the US 
Department of Defense and Intelligence Community, and is being evaluated as a mid-level 
ontology standard by IEEE (PAR3195.1).

bblocks.name: CCO Role
bblocks.abstract: A role - a realizable entity that exists because of the realization of some characteristic or set of characteristics

bblocks.name: CCO Group
bblocks.abstract: A collection of agents.

bblocks.name: CCO OccupationalRole
bblocks.abstract: A work-related role.

bblocks.name: CCO Agent
bblocks.abstract: An entity capable of performing intentional acts.

bblocks.name: CCO Organization
bblocks.abstract: An organization - a collective of persons organized for a common purpose

bblocks.name: CCO Vehicle
bblocks.abstract: An artifact designed to transport persons or cargo

bblocks.name: CCO Weapon
bblocks.abstract: An artifact designed to cause harm or damage

bblocks.name: CCO Artifact
bblocks.abstract: A material entity created or modified by human beings

bblocks.name: CCO Currency
bblocks.abstract: A system of money in use in a country

bblocks.name: CCO MonetaryAmount
bblocks.abstract: An amount of money in a specific currency

bblocks.name: CCO Process
bblocks.abstract: A continuous series of actions or changes

bblocks.name: CCO Act
bblocks.abstract: An event performed by an agent

bblocks.name: CCO Event
bblocks.abstract: A processual entity that occurs in time

bblocks.name: CCO Relation
bblocks.abstract: A relationship between entities

bblocks.name: CCO SpatialRelation
bblocks.abstract: A relationship involving spatial positioning

bblocks.name: CCO Facility
bblocks.abstract: A permanent or semi-permanent structure

bblocks.name: CCO Building
bblocks.abstract: A structure with walls and a roof

bblocks.name: CCO Infrastructure
bblocks.abstract: Basic physical systems of a region

bblocks.name: CCO SpatialRegion
bblocks.abstract: A part or region of space

bblocks.name: CCO GeodeticDatum
bblocks.abstract: A reference frame for measuring locations on Earth

bblocks.name: CCO Geospatial Location
bblocks.abstract: A location on or relative to Earth

bblocks.name: CCO Coordinates
bblocks.abstract: A set of values that specify position within a coordinate system

bblocks.name: CCO GeospatialRegion
bblocks.abstract: A three-dimensional spatial region located on or near Earth's surface

bblocks.name: CCO Coordinate System
bblocks.abstract: A system for uniquely determining position in space

bblocks.name: CCO Image
bblocks.abstract: Visual information content entity

bblocks.name: CCO Document
bblocks.abstract: A bounded information content entity

bblocks.name: CCO Dataset
bblocks.abstract: A collection of related data

bblocks.name: CCO InformationContentEntity
bblocks.abstract: An entity that consists of information

bblocks.name: CCO Identifier
bblocks.abstract: Information content entity that designates an entity

bblocks.name: CCO Text
bblocks.abstract: Textual information content entity

bblocks.name: CCO DataFile
bblocks.abstract: A digital file containing data

bblocks.name: CCO Name
bblocks.abstract: Identifier consisting of a word or phrase

bblocks.name: CCO Description
bblocks.abstract: Information content entity that describes something

bblocks.name: CCO Quality
bblocks.abstract: An attribute inhering in an entity

bblocks.name: CCO Measurement
bblocks.abstract: A quality that is assigned by measurement

bblocks.name: CCO Color
bblocks.abstract: A quality inhering in an entity by virtue of light

bblocks.name: CCO TimeInterval
bblocks.abstract: A one-dimensional temporal region

bblocks.name: CCO TimeInstant
bblocks.abstract: A zero-dimensional temporal region

bblocks.name: CCO TemporalRegion
bblocks.abstract: A region of time

bblocks.name: CCO LengthUnit
bblocks.abstract: A unit of measure for length or distance

bblocks.name: CCO MeasurementUnit
bblocks.abstract: A standard unit used to express measurements

bblocks.name: CCO Person
bblocks.abstract: A person - an agent that is a human being

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Artifact Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Artifact Ontology defines Artifacts, manufactured objects, and products

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Currency Unit Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Currency Unit Ontology defines Currency types and monetary units

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Event Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Event Ontology defines Events, processes, and temporal occurrences

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Extended Relation Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Extended Relation Ontology defines Additional relations beyond BFO

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Facility Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Facility Ontology defines Buildings, infrastructure, and constructed facilities

bblocks.name: CCO Geographic Feature
bblocks.abstract: A feature of the Earth's surface

bblocks.name: CCO Geospatial Position
bblocks.abstract: A geospatial location specified by coordinates

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Information Entity Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Information Entity Ontology defines information artifacts, documents, data, and their representations

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Quality Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Quality Ontology defines Qualities, attributes, and characteristics

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Time Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Time Ontology defines Temporal entities, instants, and intervals

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Units of Measure Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Units of Measure Ontology defines Measurement units and quantities

bblocks.name: Agent Ontology
bblocks.abstract: The Agent Ontology represents agents (especially persons and organizations) and their roles within the Common Core Ontologies framework.

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontology - Geospatial Ontology
bblocks.abstract: CCO Geospatial Ontology defines geospatial features, locations, coordinate systems, and spatial relations

bblocks.name: Common Core Ontologies
bblocks.abstract: The Common Core Ontologies (CCO) comprise eleven ontology modules that extend the Basic Formal Ontology (BFO). CCO provides a mid-level ontology framework for representing entities across multiple domains including agents, artifacts, events, facilities, geospatial features, information entities, qualities, time, units of measure, and relations.
